<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900919-0060</DOCNO><DOCID>900919-0060.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Cie. de Saint-Gobain:   Firm Seeks Approval to Lift   Its Stake in Oberland Glas</HL><DATE>09/19/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A18</SO><CO>   F.STG G.OLG</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)BUILDING MATERIALS (BLD)</IN><LP>   Cie. de Saint-Gobain said it applied for regulatoryapproval to raise its holdings in the West German glass groupOberland Glas AG above 50%, from the current level of 35%.   A spokesman for the French glass and building-materialsgroup said, however, that the move is preliminary at thisstage and might not lead to an actual increase in its stakeuntil 1991 or 1992.</LP><TEXT>   Saint-Gobain acquired its stake in Oberland in 1988through a share swap with the Wiegand family, which retains a25% interest. The French company has first refusal rights onthat 25% block, and would need prior regulatory approvalbefore it could exercise them.   Oberland couldn't immediately be reached for comment.</TEXT></DOC>